### Router CLI Reference

```ios
! Enter Global Configuration Mode
enable
configure terminal

! --- Physical Layer Setup ---
interface g 0/1
 ip address 192.168.100.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown
exit

interface g 0/2
 ip address 192.168.200.1 255.255.255.0
 no shutdown
exit

! --- DHCP Logic: Subnet 100 ---
ip dhcp pool ABC
 network 192.168.100.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.100.1
 exit
! Exclude the gateway so it isn't assigned to a PC
ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.100.1 

! --- DHCP Logic: Subnet 200 ---
ip dhcp pool DEF
 network 192.168.200.0 255.255.255.0
 default-router 192.168.200.1
 exit
ip dhcp excluded-address 192.168.200.1

! --- Commit to Memory ---
exit
write memory

```

### Troubleshooting & Verification Commands

If a PC is not receiving an IP, use these commands on the **Router** to diagnose:

* `show ip dhcp binding`: Displays which PCs have been assigned which IPs.


* `show ip dhcp pool`: Shows how many addresses are left in your pools.


* `show ip interface brief`: Verifies that the Gigabit interfaces are "Up/Up".



On the **PC Command Prompt**:

* `ipconfig /renew`: Forces the PC to ask the router for a new IP address.
